30/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Security forces discovered 65kg of explosives hidden in a car in southeast Turkey on Sunday (August 29th). 
Authorities suspect members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) planned to use it for major attacks in western Turkey. 
The materials were found in the tank of a car being inspected at a Diyarbakir entrance checkpoint. 
Three suspects, believed to be PKK members, were arrested. 
The incident happened during a unilateral ceasefire declared by the PKK through Ramadan until September 20th.
Meanwhile, the military announced on Sunday they bombarded suspected PKK positions in northern Iraq on Thursday and Friday. 
The statement did not mention casualties. 
(AFP, Zaman, Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency, AP - 29/08/10)
